or other modifications represent, as a whole, an original work of authorship.
Works that merely interact with the Software through its published interfaces
(e.g. API calls) without incorporating its source code do not constitute
Derivative Works.

"Non-Commercial Use" means use of the Software solely for personal,
educational, research, charitable, or internal organisational purposes where
no direct or indirect monetary compensation, commercial advantage, or revenue
is sought or received as a result of that use. Deploying the Software for the
benefit of a for-profit organisation's internal operations qualifies as
Non-Commercial Use provided the Software itself is not the product or service
being offered to third parties.

"Commercial Use" means any use, deployment, or distribution of the Software or
Derivative Works intended for or directed toward commercial advantage, monetary
compensation, or revenue generation, including but not limited to: selling,
reselling, sublicensing, or leasing the Software; providing the Software or
Derivative Works as a managed service (SaaS, PaaS, or similar); or bundling
the Software as a component of a commercial product or offering.

"Network Use" means making the functionality of the Software available to
third parties over a network or the Internet, whether or not any source code
is distributed.

